<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Two men have been charged after $570,000 cash and $170,000 worth of casino chips were seized as part of an investigation into corrupt betting. </p>

<p>Ziyi Liu, 27, and Hieu Duc Lam, 35, were arrested on September 9 over their alleged involvement in a baccarat betting scam at The Star casino in Sydney. </p>

<p>The NSW Police Organised Crime Squad's Casino and Racing Investigation Unit established Strike Force Antree in early September to investigate the men. </p>

<p>Police will allege Lam, a former employee at The Star casino, dealt Liu cards during three games and the men communicated to win, Sydney Morning Herald reported.   </p>

<p>Two men have been arrested and charged after allegedly conducting a betting scam (seized money pictured) during three games of baccarat at The Star Casino in Sydney </p>

<p>Police executed a search warrant on September 9 and seized over $570,000 in cash and $170,000 worth of casino chips (seized casino chips from The Star pictured) </p>

<p> Police will allege Ziyi Liu, 27, and Hieu Duc Lam, 35, were involved in corrupt betting to the value of $100,000 on September 7 and 8 at The Star casino (pictured above) </p>

<p>Liu was taken into custody at a casino car park in Sydney and Lam was also arrested at home at Canley Heights in western Sydney.   </p>

<p>Police executed a search warrant at the Canley Heights home and seized over $270,000 in cash, $2000 in US dollars and electronic storage devices.  </p>

<p>Another search warrant was carried out at a unit at Ryde, where investigators seized over $300,000 cash and casino chips valued at $169,000.  </p>

<p>Both men were charged with three counts of dishonestly obtaining financial advantage by deception and participating in a criminal group contributing criminal activity. </p>

<p>Liu appear at Downing Centre Local Court on Wednesday where he entered pleas of not guilty to all charges, The Daily Telegraph reported. </p>

<p>Court documents alleged Liu cheated on three occasions while he was playing baccarat between September 7 and 8.</p>

<p>He allegedly pocketed sums of $24,000, $32,000 and $44,000 and will appear again at Downing Centre Local Court on November 11.    </p>

<p>Both men were charged with dishonestly obtaining financial advantage by deception and participating in a criminal group contributing criminal activity (seized chip pictured) </p>

<p>Liu appear at Downing Centre Local Court on Wednesday where he entered pleas of not guilty to all charges (seized cash allegedly part of the casino scam pictured) </p>

<p>Both men have been granted strict conditional bail and set to appear at the Downing Centre Local Court on November 11 (cash found during the NSW Police search pictured) </p>

<p>Lam appeared at Liverpool Local Court on Wednesday and his matter was adjourned to Downing Centre Local Court on November 11.  </p>

<p>Police will allege the men were involved in corrupt betting to the value of $100,000 and further charges are expected to be laid.</p>

<p>Both men have been granted strict conditional bail.  </p>

<p>The organised crime squad's casino and racing investigation unit acting Detective Inspector John Cosgrove said their scam was quickly noticed. </p>

<p>'These types of things were picked up fairly quickly with the systems and processes at the casino and the police investigated that, and gathered the evidence to put these men before the court.</p>

<p>'In general terms, there is a lot of cameras, you are under constant video surveillance down there and your actions and your movements are being continually monitored,' he said.  </p>

<p>Investigations under Strike Force Antree are continuing </p>

<p>A spokesperson from The Star told Daily Mail Australia 'The Star's internal processes identified an issue and law enforcement was subsequently engaged.'</p>

<p>'The casino regulator was also informed,' the spokesperson said. </p>

<p>Liu allegedly pocketed sums of $24,000, $32,000 and $44,000 during the baccarat game (items seized during the police raid pictured above) </p>
